The paper proposes a topological technique for detecting dimensions from point samples, which involves computing local homology using Vietoris-Rips complexes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), machine learning (cs.LG), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.CG and cs.DS seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with geometric and topological structures and their computation. However, the paper also discusses the use of computational topology and machine learning techniques, which could make cs.LG and cs.SI relevant as well.
